Original finish, with bullet feed ramp parkerized, which is correct for this serial range Ithaca. For reasons unknown, the milling of feed ramps was omitted on pistols shipped in December 1944 and January 1945 in the serial range from about 2100000 through 2134403, thus, the finish remained on the feed ramp. Correct Ordnance Department "crossed cannon" final inspection mark. Correct Army Inspector of Ordnance stamp "FJA", (for Frank J. Atwood). Correct matching "P" proof marks on slide and receiver. Correct Ithaca factory proof mark, on left side of receiver on trigger guard, as pictured. Correct Ithaca serrated hammer. Correct stamped trigger. Correct late war Ithaca 8-rib mainspring housing. Correct High Standard barrel, with original blue finish, and excellent bore. Correct grip stocks by Keyes Fibre Co. Comes with one correct WWII magazine made by Scovill Mfg. Course Duration
8 hours of combined classroom instructions and qualification testing.

Mandatory Range Equipment to Qualify

($20.00 ea. + shipping)Factory info:The AK30 is constructed of proprietary aerospace polymers, and sets itself apart from other polymer magazines with its purpose-built design and multiple unique features.By eliminating the removable floor plate we created a stronger design; a five-sided box. This revolutionary design, paired with our advanced polymers gives the AK30 the strength it needs to survive impacts that would destroy other magazines. After the magazine is molded, the body and end-cap are bonded together, so no disassembly is possible or required. The AK30 has a unique low-friction semi-floating follower that is slotted to allow for easy cleaning and hassle-free maintenance. Just dunk the magazine in hot soapy water, rinse and invert to drain. Dry contamination easily flows free through the vented follower design. The AK30 also features a Mil-Spec spring that is heat-treated and stress relieved.Internal designInside, there is a lot going on! The locking surfaces are reinforced by a stainless steel cage that has been molded into the entire top of the magazine to further ensure reliability for years of trouble free service. We purposely omitted reinforcing the feed-lips with metal, being as our polymer rebounds back to its original shape much more reliably than metal or metal reinforced designs. When examined, the benefit of steel reinforced feed lips was found to be less desirable, as the two dissimilar materials, polymer and steel rebound and flex at differing rates. This can cause delamination between the two materials, which can create an environment for malfunctions. It was also observed that even though the AKM platform is field proven and very robust, attempts at field repairing bent feed lips by end users were unsuccessful.External DesignOutside, our design team created a magazine that can be utilized by an operator in any environmental condition. The aggressive ridges on the front and rear allow a positive purchase when seating the AK30 into the rifle. The deep waffle pattern on the magazine sides assist in rapid extraction from magazine pouches, and 100% positive manipulation within conditions beyond extreme. Every surface of the AK30 was given careful consideration to benefit the operator working in the harshest conditions on earth.Platform SpecificsInitially designed to fit AKM-47 rifles that use detachable double-stack magazines, the AK30 has been successfully deployed in other makes and models similar to the AKM as well. We still advise users of mass-produced/domestically produced rifles to test their individual rifles for compatibility, as there exists a very wide set of “standards” to which rifles are manufactured, and in the rare occasion, the AK30 may be too dimensionally specific to accommodate for a wide tolerance stacking issue.NOTE:We will NOT ship to any state that has a ban / restriction on High Capacity magazines such as:Calf. , Colorado, Conn., Washington DC, Hawii, Illionois, Maryland, New jersey, New York, ect.

Hello - I have 4 complete unopened cases (2 tin of 440rds each) of 7N1 7.62x54r Soviet Spetnaz sniper ammo for the Dragunov or Tiger SVD's but can also be used in Mosin Nagants. These are popular for the match grade accuracy and the steel core penetrators within. These are no longer imported and very sought after.

As for why I am parting with them...I sold my dragunov over a year ago and the purchaser wished to pick up the remaining ammunition at a later date. Since he has been not heard of for over a year, they are back up for sale.

I will not open a case since the bands are intact but if you wish to open upon purchase for inspection I'm completely comfortable with that. I will not split a case. I would prefer not to ship. Local sale only. $750 a case firm (2 tins). No discount for purchasing all 4 cases. I can meet in the Bonney Lake/Buckley area.  I will also accept pre-1964 US coins (junk silver) at spot price as partial/full payment.

For those who do not know what the 7N1 is, this is not your common 7.62x54r. Here's a tin (1 tin, not a case) on gunbroker as an example.
